EasyJet Says It Rejects EasyGroup’s Allegations

-- B y   D a v i d   A l t a n e r
-- 
2011-07-27T07:12:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/easyjet-says-it-rejects-easygroup-s-allegations-correct-.html
(Corrects to show statement was issued on July 18.)  EasyJet Plc (EZJ)  said in a statement
dated July 18 that it responded to EasyGroup’s letter of July
11, repeating its position that its January fleet announcement
complied with listing rules and fell below the threshold for
transactions requiring shareholder approval. EasyJet said it
also rejected all of EasyGroup’s allegations of wrongdoing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Altaner in London at 
 daltaner@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chris Peterson at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  